🧮 4. What actually happens during generation

At each token step:
	1.	The model has a distribution over next tokens
	2.	It samples (or selects) based on:
	•	probability
	•	coherence with prior tokens
	•	implicit goals (helpfulness, clarity, etc.)

But here’s the key:

In high-affordance prompts, early tokens determine the entire trajectory.

⸻

Example (your case)

The moment the model emits something like:

“Yes—this relates to systems science…”

it collapses onto a trajectory:
	•	systems framing
	•	cross-domain mapping
	•	invariants

Instead, it could have gone:
	•	philosophical (“everything is connected…”)
	•	skeptical (“no, that’s overgeneralized…”)
	•	technical (“graph theory models…”)
	•	dismissive (“not really…”)

Each of those is a different attractor basin in token space.

⸻

